						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Bottom side of the stone now used as door frame of the central shrine of the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>10th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 9 • • • Amāvāsyā,</hi> the other details being lost. The date cannot be verified. The characters are of about <hi rend="bold">10th Century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>The inscription mentions Āychapayya and Niṁbadēva-Bhaṭṭa. The details of gift cannot be made out.</p>						

						</summary>
